			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Fellow Archers!!
<br />

<br />
Ill try and make this as short as possible.  I love the Scout class: however, some issues to be discussed.
<br />
Scouts have low Str.  Please remember this thru out my long and boring post.  With armor and a few bundles of arrows not much room to Carry loot.  And forgive me if im wrong please, but most times we Pull for the group and Have to be quick on the feet.  Saying this Here are some Issues.
<br />
- its 2 lb per bundle of 20 arrows. (Ever hold 20 arrows?  Does it weight as much has a Bastard Sword?  I think Not)
<br />
- Player made arrows have no Extra Benifit Other than a little cheaper.  Why not Better accuracy or Maybe make em lighter? 
<br />
- I dont mind Paying for arrows.  Money is easy to get.  Other classes get Free spells and such for killing mobs and Players can at least sell their weapon back to the merchant when they have out leveled it.  Why are arrows so Costly?  Come on please Give us a Break.
<br />
- This is A Big Big Gripe.  Im a Fletcher.  I cant make Flight arrows out in the Field when im Hunting. Have to use a Forge to making the best arrows I can use.  This sucks. I cant be as effective to group Using lower Skilled arrows. To explain.  If you make your Arrows while hunting you can carry more supplies.  I can make hundreds of arrows with some wood and feathers. Lower Weight and takes less room in inventory. 3/4 of one bag I have is used just to hold Arrows.  Why limit the scouts?
<br />
- Quivers?  Thought they were gonna be implemented.
<br />
- Tracking?  Same.
<br />

<br />
To sum up... I posted here to get some Group Brain storming going.  This is not a Ranger EQ rant.  Oh No!!  DaoC did a great job making the Scout class.  Now I wanna Play a Scout.  Not running to the merchant all the time.  If Ive missed something tell me.  I love this Scout class.  Cant wait to Shoot more of our Enemies.  But Hey!!  Why go far away to Hunt when the 80 arrows I carry will make me to fat to walk.  Help me guys Give me some Input. Before you ask Yes I put 10 pts in str when I made my Character.
<br />

<br />
Level 15 Beta Scout
<br />
Newbie Scout one new server.
<br />

<br />
Larken</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
